# <type>(<scope>): <subject>
#
# <body>
#
# <footer>

# Type should be one of the following:
# * feat (new feature)
# * fix (bug fix)
# * docs (documentation)
# * style (formatting, no code change)
# * refactor (refactoring production code)
# * test (adding tests, refactoring test)
# * chore (updating build process, etc., no production code change)

# Scope is optional and should be noun describing section of codebase
# Examples: auth, api, ui, database

# Subject should use imperative mood and not end with period
# No more than 50 characters

# Body should include motivation for change and contrast with previous behavior
# Wrap at 72 characters

# Footer should reference issues and include breaking changes
# Examples:
# Fixes #123
# BREAKING CHANGE: API endpoint /users now requires authentication